- Although the AOR disc provides some elements I enjoy (warm tape, piano detail), those are outweighed by its structural and mixing choices that run counter to multiple explicit dislikes. Highway to Hell, despite being rawer and less orchestral, better satisfies the centerpiece of my listening priorities: dynamic, rhythm‑driven, warm analogue rock with punch and presence.

